From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Slothful Dev <dev@slothfulchat.invalid>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 19:26:46 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 19/19] group admins: admin groups where only the creator
 manages the group
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Port of ArcaneChat's group-admin feature (ArcaneChat/core PR #438,
commits c9b9666 + a2683e9) onto chatmail core:

- create_group_with_admin() creates a group whose grpid is
  FINGERPRINT:RANDOMID — the embedded key fingerprint marks the admin.
- Only the admin may add/remove members, rename, change description,
  avatar and the ephemeral-message timer; core enforces this both when
  sending (ensure!) and when receiving (non-admin group-change messages
  are ignored/trashed).
- Securejoin: invite QR carries the admin fingerprint (z= instead of
  g= for the group name); non-admins abort handshakes that would add
  members.
- The admin may delete other members' messages for everyone; receivers
  accept a deletion of somebody else's message only from the admin.
  (Deviation from ArcaneChat: their receive-side check accidentally let
  *any* member of a *regular* group delete others' messages, because
  is_group_admin_contact() returns true when the group has no admin;
  we gate on the group actually being an admin group.)
- New JSON-RPC: create_group_with_admin, FullChat.groupAdminId.
